words: I was still depressed. That's that. That's how it works. And I
kind of turned into a hermit in college, a little bit low key
hermit because I really didn't like the people that I lived in the hall with.
I lived in the LGBT hall, and they are wild partiers,
and I just wanted to be in my room, hang out, maybe watch Netflix or something,
talk to maybe one person. My roommate started to get really annoying because she was, like,
hanging out with people in the room, so I just kind of hide it away from everyone. I was really alienated,
and I just hated my life. It was so quick,
such a huge reversal of how I felt one week earlier,
